## 1. Critical Bugs & Stability

### 1.1 WDT Crash on Screen Switch (Left/Right)

- [x] Root cause: `update_outlined_text()` writes 10 labels without yielding,
      starving IDLE0 on CPU0 → WDT fires ~5 seconds after switching to ODO
- [x] Guard: only update ODO labels when ODO screen is active
- [x] Rate-limit ODO updates to 1/second (20 ticks × 50ms)
- [x] Add `taskYIELD()` between the two `update_outlined_text()` calls
- [x] Skip `lv_label_set_text()` if text hasn't changed (avoids invalidation storm)
- [x] UI task now wraps `lv_timer_handler()` in LVGL mutex lock/unlock
- [ ] Stress test: rapid button pressing for 60+ seconds (verify no WDT)
- [ ] Consider replacing 4-shadow outlined text with 1 shadow for lighter rendering

### 1.2 GT911 Touch Not Detected (All Projects)

- [x] Added GT911 hardware reset via TCA9554 EXIO2 before I2C probe
- [x] Probe both GT911 addresses: 0x5D and 0x14
- [!] **INT pin conflict:** GT911 INT may be on GPIO16 — same as I2C slave SCL.
      Need to verify against board schematic and resolve conflict.
- [ ] Register GT911 as LVGL input device (full touch support)
- [ ] Add `esp_lcd_touch_gt911` managed component to `idf_component.yml`
- [ ] Test touch across all board revisions
- [ ] Apply GT911 fix to center/ and gps/ (different hardware, different touch init)

### 1.3 Left Display Flicker During UART Debug Logging

- [x] Root cause identified: 100Hz `ESP_LOGI` per parsed frame saturates UART0
      console and starves LCD refresh task
- [x] Fixed: `OPENDASH_UART_DEBUG` set to 0 (compile flag in `opendash_uart.h`)
- [x] "STX+TAG detected" log downgraded to `ESP_LOGD`
- [x] 5-second heartbeat retained at `ESP_LOGI` for passive health monitoring

### 1.4 Bad ETX Frame Loss (~15-20%)

- [~] False `STX+TAG` (0x02 0x5F) in 35-byte VR6 zero-padding triggers
      false frame starts → misaligned reads → ETX mismatch
- [ ] Implement frame timing validation (expect frames every ~10ms)
- [ ] Track consecutive good frames to increase sync confidence
- [ ] Consider checksum/CRC validation of parsed fields (plausibility check)

