### 5.2 Multidisplay UART (HC-05 Bluetooth)

> **MD Output Rate:** SERIALFREQ=10 (10ms) = **100 Hz** default.
> OpenDash UART RX keeps up at 100 Hz but the main loop only consumes at
> **5 Hz** (every 200ms). 95% of frames are discarded (latest value kept).
> Consider lowering SERIALFREQ to 50 (20 Hz) or 100 (10 Hz) on the MD side
> to save ATmega2560 CPU cycles with zero data loss. Changeable at runtime
> via MD serial command 11, persisted to EEPROM addr 101.
>
> **Bad ETX (~15-20%) is NOT timing-related** — it's electrical noise/byte
> corruption on the BT UART link. The parser handles it gracefully by
> re-scanning for STX.

- [x] Binary frame parser: STX(0x02) TAG(0x5F) payload[93] ETX(0x03)
- [x] Little-endian AVR field extraction (rd_u16, rd_s16, rd_u32)
